文献ID: STP681-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_4th Volume_030_chunk1
证据片段: CANDU (CANada Deuterium Uranium) fuel elements are fabricated with Zircaloy-4 sheaths in the cold-worked and stress-relieved condition.

文献ID: STP681-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_4th Volume_030_chunk1
证据片段: During fabrication, one or more regions, about $5 0 \ \mathrm { m m }$ long, are subjected to a $\beta$ heat treatment during a brazing operation to attach bearing or spacer pads. The brazing cycle involves heating the sheath to about $1 0 5 0 ^ { \circ } \mathrm { C }$ for a few seconds followed by cooling at a rate of about $4 0 ^ { \circ } \mathbf { C } \thinspace \thinspace \mathbf { s } ^ { \textrm { - 1 } }$ .

文献ID: STP681-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_4th Volume_030_chunk1
证据片段: Dimensions were nominally $1 5 . 2 5 \ \mathrm { \ m m }$ outside diameter by $0 . 4 5 ~ \mathrm { m m }$ wall by $5 0 0 ~ \mathrm { { m m } }$ long.

文献ID: STP681-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_4th Volume_030_chunk1
证据片段: Onehalf-metre lengths of fuel sheath were internally pressurized and resistance heated in vacuum at nominal heating rates of 0.5 or $2 5 ^ { \circ } \mathbf { C } \thinspace \mathbf { s } ^ { - 1 }$ The pressure was held constant to within $\pm 0 . 0 2 \ \mathrm { M P a }$

文献ID: STP681-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_4th Volume_030_chunk1
证据片段: In this cycle, the sheath was heated in vacuum to $1 0 5 0 ^ { \circ } \mathrm { C }$ in $4 0 \thinspace s$ , held at this temperature for $2 0 \thinspace s$ , and then cooled. The initial cooling rate through the two-phase temperature region was about 35 to $4 0 ^ { \circ } \mathbf { C } \thinspace \thinspace \mathbf { s } ^ { - 1 }$ .

文献ID: STP681-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_4th Volume_030_chunk1
证据片段: The initial cooling rate through the two-phase temperature region was about 35 to $4 0 ^ { \circ } \mathbf { C } \thinspace \thinspace \mathbf { s } ^ { - 1 }$ .
